{
  "texts": [
    "This approach, which falls between supervised and unsupervised learning, uses unlabeled and labeled values as training data.",
    "When combined with a modest quantity of labeled data, the learning accuracy of unlabeled data improves significantly.",
    "In theory, the data adjacent to it have the same name.",
    "Likewise, the cluster assumption, which states that every data in a cluster is the same, has a similar name [44].",
    "Also, rather than using the whole input space, the data are limited to a single dimension."
  ]
}